This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with video-based driving behavior recognition using a two-stream CNN framework. It also involves deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in the computer vision field. 

The paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it employs a deep learning model for behavior recognition. 

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with automated recognition of driving behavior. 

Robotics (cs.RO) is also a likely sub-category as the paper's focus on driving behavior recognition has implications for autonomous vehicles and robotics. 

Finally, the paper may belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category as it mentions the importance of driving behavior surveillance for traffic security and public management.
